'''James Cosmo''' (born 24 May 1948) is a Scottish actor. He is best known for playing older, veteran warriors in historical dramas and epics, such as Campbell in ''[[wikipedia:Braveheart|Braveheart]]'', Glaucus in ''[[wikipedia:Troy (film)|Troy]]'' (written by [[David Benioff]]), Hrothgar in ''[[wikipedia:The Last Legion|The Last Legion]]'' and Hengist in the British TV series ''[[wikipedia:Merlin (TV series)|Merlin]]''. His other roles include ''[[wikipedia:The Chronicles of Narnia: The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe|The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe]]'' (as [[wikipedia:Father Christmas|Father Christmas]]) and recent guest roles on American TV series ''[[wikipedia:FlashForward (TV series)|FlashForward]]'', ''[[wikipedia:Castle (TV series)|Castle]]'' and ''[[wikipedia:Sons of Anarchy|Sons of Anarchy]]''.

In ''[[Game of Thrones]]'' Cosmo is playing [[Jeor Mormont]], the Old Bear. He was confirmed in the role on 16 July 2010. He initially appeared as a guest star in the [[Season 1|first season]] and joined the starring cast for the [[Season 2|second season]]. He also voices the role of Jeor Mormont in the ''Game of Thrones'' role-playing [[Game of Thrones (computer game)|computer game]].

The last scene Cosmo filmed was the opening scene of the first episode of [[Season 3]], when he burns the [[wight]] and saves Samwell Tarly.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.accesshollywood.com/game-of-thrones-james-cosmo-talks-lord-commander-mormonts-dramatic-scene-at-crasters-keep-spoiler-alert_article_78360 Game Of Thrones: James Cosmo Talks Lord Commander Mormontâ&euro;&trade;s Dramatic Scene At Crasterâ&euro;&trade;s Keep]&lt;/ref&gt;
